ions"},{"source":"recFmZAYBt5nsYMPF","target":"recL1WV82pXaRBQ59","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recFmZAYBt5nsYMPF","target":"rec5pDuWtEaOK7ehk","label":"event"}],"verses":[{"id":"rect7T83ncSoi4zh6","ref":"Jer.38.1","text":"Then Shephatiah the son of Mattan, and Gedaliah the son of Pashur, and Jucal the son of Shelemiah, and Pashur the son of Malchiah, heard the words that Jeremiah had spoken unto all the people, saying,","year":-598},{"id":"recAqhViu3USFiZiC","ref":"Jer.38.2","text":"Thus saith the LORD, He that remaineth in this city shall die by the sword, by the famine, and by the pestilence: but he that goeth forth to the Chaldeans shall live; for he shall have his life for a prey, and shall live.","year":-598},{"id":"recg0ndeo0fJ8C7NB","ref":"Jer.38.3","text":"Thus saith the LORD, This city shall surely be given into the hand of the king of Babylon’s army, which shall take it.","year":-598},{"id":"recsdINFCXraJPEi4","ref":"Jer.38.4","text":"Therefore the princes said unto the king, We beseech thee, let this man be put to death: for thus he weakeneth the hands of the men of war that remain in this city, and the hands of all the people, in speaking such words unto them: for this man seeketh not the welfare of this people, but the hurt.","year":-598},{"id":"recCBSnLChjDz7aJI","ref":"Jer.38.5","text":"Then Zedekiah the king said, Behold, he is in your hand: for the king is not he that can do any thing against you.","year":-598},{"id":"recUbbNHv7FRBAdJ3","ref":"Jer.38.6","text":"Then took they Jeremiah, and cast him into the dungeon of Malchiah the son of Hammelech, that was in the court of the prison: and they let down Jeremiah with cords. And in the dungeon there was no water, but mire: so Jeremiah sunk in the mire.","year":-598},{"id":"recLqXvaGKXRS4Hz9","ref":"Jer.38.7","text":"Now when Ebedmelech the Ethiopian, one of the eunuchs which was in the king’s house, heard that they had put Jeremiah in the dungeon; the king then sitting in the gate of Benjamin;","year":-598},{"id":"recDQHLaTmI9OfNQX","ref":"Jer.38.8","text":"Ebedmelech went forth out of the king’s house, and spake to the king, saying,","year":-598}]}
